bsite=indiatv|author=| date=17 March 2020}}</ref> [[Chandigarh]] administration ordered the closure of shopping malls, cinema halls, gyms, nightclubs, swimming pools, coaching centres, spas, creches and video game parlours till 31 March. It also banned gatherings of more than a 100 people and census work was postponed.<ref>{{cite web |title=Covid-19: Malls, cinema halls, gyms closed in Chandigarh| url=https://m.hindustantimes.com/cities/malls-clubs-discotheques-and-gyms-closed-in-chandigarh-till-march-31-to-check-coronavirus-spread/story-SlWceuV22oQXG5RKxODz4M.html|website=Hindustan times|author=| date=16 March 2020}}</ref> At the same time, [[Dera]] chiefs were asked to postpone all religious events till 31 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Punjab malls, gyms, restaurants deserted after advisory on coronavirus| url=https://wap.business-standard.com/multimedia/video-gallery/general/punjab-malls-gyms-restaurants-deserted-after-advisory-on-coronavirus-101227.htm|newspaper=Business Standard India|author=}}</ref> The GoM has also directed that no more than 50 people are allowed to gather at any place other than [[weddings]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Punjab: Malls, shopping complexes shut till March 31; curbs on gatherings at marriage palaces| url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/north-and-central/punjab-malls-shopping-complexes-shut-till-march-31-curbs-on-gatherings-at-marriage-palaces-814691.html|website=Deccan herald|author=| date=17 March 2020}}</ref> [[Pondicherry]] shut down schools, colleges, cinemas and gyms till 31 March.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/coronavirus-live-updates-number-of-coronavirus-cases-in-india-mumbai-hyderabad-kerala-pune-delhi/liveblog/74664459.cms|title=Coronavirus outbreak live updates: Railways cancels 76 trains as coronavirus precautionary measure, non-occupancy|date=|work=Times of India|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Mumbai Police]] ordered the closure of pubs, bars and discotheques till 31 March.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/mumbai/coronavirus-in-mumbai-eatery-industry-seeks-financial-relief-from-government/articleshow/74682915.cms |website=Times of India |accessdate=18 March 2020|date=18 March 2020|title=Coronavirus in Mumbai: Pubs, bars closed |first1=Reeba |last1=Zachariah |first2=S Ahmed |last2=Ali}}</ref>\n*'''On 18 March,''' [[District magistrate|district magistrate and deputy commissioner]] of [[Srinagar district]] in [[Jammu and Kashmir (union territory)|Jammu and Kashmir]] said that the entry of all foreign tourists has been banned in the entire union territory.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Foreign tourists' entry banned in Kashmir| url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/coronavirus-foreign-tourists-entry-banned-in-kashmir20200318043955/|website=ANI|author=}}</ref> On the other hand, the Directorate of Floriculture, Parks and Horticulture of the state has also extended the [[Bahu Fort|Bagh-e-Bahu Garden]] to the general public from 18 to 31 March to keep the situation under control in the Union Territory.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Entry of foreign tourists banned in Kashmir| url=https://m.timesofindia.com/india/coronavirus-entry-of-foreign-tourists-banned-in-kashmir/amp_articleshow/74680062.cms|website=timesofindia|author=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Foreign tourists' entry banned in Kashmir| url=https://in.news.yahoo.com/coronavirus-foreign-tourists-entry-banned-kashmir-230952993.html?guccounter=1&guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS8&guce_referrer_sig=AQAAAAsTPJ7Iu8cHV2-xuPg420W0USOlXiZxrTxRaDzUOSe5JdhiIz3IZSoNue88uIJ6prDuoXqZJARg2C8LnSYSxIymW9gjjnnnAAptcCa3E3BOPUOfZxHBFR2hFOPpN5U7HP3MFvt6wIV-_j4WcRlVUxq_FjHwkZKTOgU_NrfcszhK|website=Yahoo india|author=}}</ref> [[Government of Andhra Pradesh]] announced closure of all educational institutions till 31 March.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/education/news/andhra-pradesh-educatio